{"title_page": "Presidential Flight (UAE)", "text_new": "{{Infobox Airline \n|airline=Presidential Flight\n|logo=\n|logo_size=\n|IATA=MO\n|ICAO=AUH\n|callsign=SULTAN\n|headquarters=[[Abu Dhabi]], [[United Arab Emirates]]\n|parent=\n|founded=\n|key_people=\n|bases=[[Abu Dhabi International Airport]]\n|focus_cities=\n|frequent_flyer=\n|lounge=\n|alliance=\n|fleet_size=8\n|destinations=\n|website=http://pf.ae\n}}\n\n'''Presidential Flight''' is the organization responsible for air transport of the [[government]] of [[Abu Dhabi]], [[United Arab Emirates]]. The airline previously operated under the name ''Abu Dhabi Amiri Flight'' and changed its name to ''Presidential Flight'' on 16 February 2009.<ref>{{cite web |title=Presidential Flight |url=http://pf.ae |website=pf.ae |accessdate=19 February 2019 |language=en}}</ref>\n\n==Fleet==\n[[File:Dubai Air Wing Airbus A300 PER Wheatley.jpg|thumb|right|300px|[[Airbus A300|Airbus A300-600R]] of the Presidential Flight at [[Perth Airport]], [[Australia]] in 1990s.]]\nThe Presidential Flight fleet consists of the following aircraft (as of December 7, 2019):<ref name=\"planespotters2019\">{{cite web |title=Presidential Flight Fleet Details and History |url=http://www.planespotters.net/airline/Presidential-Flight |website=www.planespotters.net |accessdate=20 February 2019 |language=en}}</ref>\n\n<center>\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"margin:0.5em auto;text-align:center\"\n|+ '''Presidential Flight Current Fleet'''\n!style=\"width:165px;\" |<abbr title=\"Type of Aircraft\">Aircraft</abbr>\n!style=\"width:55px;\" |<abbr title=\"Current Total Number In Fleet\">Total</abbr>\n!style=\"width:55px;\" |<abbr title=\"Number of Firm Orders\">Orders</abbr>\n!style=\"width:165px;\" |Notes\n|-\n|[[Airbus A320-200]]\n|1\n|&mdash;\n|\n|- \n|[[Boeing Business Jet|Boeing 737-800/BBJ2]]\n|1\n|&mdash;\n|\n|-\n|[[Boeing 777-200ER]]\n|1\n|&mdash;\n|\n|-\n|[[Boeing 777-300ER]]\n|1\n|&mdash;\n|\n|-\n|[[Boeing 787-8]]\n|1\n|&mdash;\n|\n|-\n|[[Boeing 787-